        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Ephesus, or 11 miles
northwest of Franklin, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ephesus, Centralhatchee, Roopville, Frolona, Tyus, Blackjack
Mountain, and Roosterville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
